channel.description:
Hi guys! 

When I navigating from the Blog page to the Homepage, it will show a blank page. 
Happened on my live site. see this screen capture video [here](https://imgur.com/a/r3fwduh)
and this error appears:
![8799C75A-B600-4FC3-8E8F-A36B24F90EFE|690x493](upload://9nCiC8NB7orOENuBjqw54H6ELeQ.jpeg)
![73A2F018-4466-4220-8575-F8E3CFA66FBD|681x500](upload://trFvPiTpje0WLXNjEauCUjCfvD7.jpeg)


On my local build production server (with `npm run serve`), it works great! see this screen capture video [here](https://imgur.com/a/4tBQI9s). 
I can't debug it since I can't replicate the error on my local. 
sorry I hidden some information but here is my frontity.settings.js file:
```
const settings = {
  name: "",
  state: {
    frontity: {
      url: "",
      title: "",
      description:"",
    },
  },
  packages: [
    {
      name: "",
    },
    {
      name: "@frontity/wp-source",
      state: {
        source: {
          url: "",
          homepage: "/home",
          postsPage: "/blog",
        },
      },
    },
    "frontity-share",
    "@frontity/tiny-router",
    "@frontity/html2react",
    "@vulcancreative/frontity-contact-form-7",
    "@frontity/head-tags",
  ],
};

export default settings;

```
Any help will be much appreciated! Thanks
